# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Overlapp environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the values. `.env.local` is
# gitignored — never commit real keys. Restart `next dev` after editing.
# On Vercel, set these in Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── REQUIRED (Supabase) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase project URL. Dashboard → Project Settings → API → "Project URL".
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=

# Supabase anon / publishable key (safe for the browser; RLS is the real guard).
# Dashboard → Project Settings → API → anon / public (or the sb_publishable_… key).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# Public base URL of the app — used for auth email redirects, invite links, AND
# the Google/Microsoft OAuth redirect URIs. Local dev: http://localhost:3000 ·
# Prod: your deployed origin (must match the host of the redirect URIs below).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ── SERVER-ONLY secrets (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix → never sent to the browser) ──

# Service-role key. Bypasses RLS — used by the calendar-sync worker (to manage
# tokens + events) and account deletion. Dashboard → API → service_role
# (or sb_secret_…). ⚠️ Treat like a root password. Never expose / commit.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ── Phase 2: Google Calendar sync (LIVE — fill these to enable Connect) ──────
# Full walkthrough: docs/GOOGLE-SETUP.md.
# Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → OAuth 2.0 client (Web).
# The client's Authorized redirect URI must be EXACTLY:
#   ${NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL}/api/calendars/google/callback
#   (local: http://localhost:3000/api/calendars/google/callback)
# Leave blank → the Calendars page shows a "not configured" notice; the rest of
# the app is unaffected.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Background re-sync secret (app/api/cron/sync-calendars). Generate with
# `openssl rand -hex 32`. On Vercel, when this is set the platform automatically
# sends it as the cron's `Authorization: Bearer …` header. Required only once you
# deploy + want scheduled re-sync (the Connect + "Sync now" paths don't need it).
CRON_SECRET=

# ── Phase 6: Microsoft Graph / Outlook calendar sync (the Google twin) ───────
# Full walkthrough: docs/MICROSOFT-SETUP.md.
# Azure Portal → App registrations → your app → "Certificates & secrets" (secret)
# + "Authentication" (Web redirect URI). The redirect URI must be EXACTLY:
#   ${NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL}/api/calendars/microsoft/callback
#   (local: http://localhost:3000/api/calendars/microsoft/callback)
# Leave blank → the Calendars page just omits the "Connect Microsoft" button.
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Optional. Which Microsoft accounts may connect: `common` (work + personal,
# default), `organizations`, `consumers`, or a specific tenant (directory) ID.
# MICROSOFT_TENANT=common

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEFERRED — leave blank until the relevant phase. Listed so the shape is known.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Later: Apple CalDAV / ICS ──

# ── Phase 4: Web Push (VAPID keys) ──
# Generate a keypair with: `node -e "console.log(require('web-push').generateVAPIDKeys())"`
# The PUBLIC key is exposed to the browser (NEXT_PUBLIC_) to subscribe a device;
# the PRIVATE key signs pushes server-side (never bundled). VAPID_SUBJECT is a
# mailto: or https: contact URL required by the Web Push spec. Absent → push is
# silently disabled (the UI shows "push not configured"; the app is unaffected).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=
# VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY=
# VAPID_SUBJECT=mailto:you@example.com

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT an app env var — configured in the Supabase dashboard, not here:
#   • Resend (auth email) → Dashboard → Authentication → SMTP Settings.
#   • Google OAuth *login* provider → Dashboard → Authentication → Providers
#     (separate from the Phase 2 calendar OAuth above).
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
